From: ask2 PR14z19 <ask2@local>
Date: Sat, 23 May 2026 06:09:00 +0000
Subject: ask: in-tree skeleton (drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/dpaa/ask/)

PR14z19 Path A stage 1 of the in-tree migration plan
(plans/PR14z19-PATH-A-DESIGN.md and the agent-session stages 1-6
plan).  This patch is intentionally skeleton-only: it creates a new
in-tree directory drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/dpaa/ask/ with a
single fs_initcall driver that prints a one-line banner.  No real
ASK source is migrated yet; stage 2 (patch 0048) does that.

Why an in-tree directory at all: the ASK pre-netdev hook (patch 0044,
fman_pcd_register_pre_netdev_hook) MUST be installed before
dpaa_eth_probe runs.  dpaa_eth_probe fires from device_initcall, so
ASK has to be earlier than device_initcall -> fs_initcall.  Loadable
modules' module_init runs after device_initcall, which is structurally
too late.  Therefore ASK must be built-in, which requires its source
to live inside the kernel tree (Kconfig bool, not tristate).

Layout:

  drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/dpaa/
  +- Kconfig         : adds nested source of ask/Kconfig
  +- Makefile        : adds obj-$(CONFIG_FSL_DPAA_ASK) += ask/
  +- ask/
     +- Kconfig      : config FSL_DPAA_ASK (bool, default n,
     |                  depends on FSL_DPAA_ETH && FSL_FMAN_PCD)
     +- Makefile     : ask-objs := ask_main.o  (stage 2 expands this)
     +- ask_main.c   : fs_initcall printing
                       "ask: in-tree skeleton present
                        (version 2.0.0-stage1-skeleton, fs_initcall)"

No functional behaviour: the fs_initcall is a no-op modulo the banner
print.  Verifies only that the Kbuild plumbing
(CONFIG_FSL_DPAA_ASK=y -> ask/built-in.a -> vmlinux) is correct.
Stage 2 (patch 0048) copies the real ~5600 LOC of ASK source from
kernel/flavors/ask/oot-modules/ask/ into this directory.  Stage 3
(patch 0049) wires Path A by replacing this fs_initcall's body with
fman_pcd_register_pre_netdev_hook(&ask_pcd_install_cb).

Build-verified:
  $ make ARCH=arm64 CROSS_COMPILE=aarch64-linux-gnu- LOCALVERSION=-vyos \
        drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/dpaa/ask/
  CC      drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/dpaa/ask/ask_main.o
  AR      drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/dpaa/ask/built-in.a
  (zero warnings, zero errors)

Signed-off-by: ask2 PR14z19 <ask2@local>

